ZH: 请你相信我的善意。
EN: Please believe in my good intentions.

ZH: 这是一份善意的警告。
EN: This is a warning made out of good intentions.

ZH: 他的建议都是出于善意。
EN: His suggestions are all made with good intentions.

ZH: 她的行为充满善意。
EN: Her actions are filled with goodwill.

ZH: 我们应该给予他们善意的支持。
EN: We should give them our support in good faith.

ZH: 我衷心感谢你们的善意。
EN: I sincerely appreciate your goodwill.

ZH: 请你不要误解我的善意。
EN: Please don't misunderstand my good intentions.

ZH: 我希望我们能以善意的方式处理问题。
EN: I hope we can handle the problem in a good-hearted manner.

ZH: 我们要用善意去对待每个人。
EN: We should treat everyone with goodwill.

ZH: 这个计划是出于善意而制定的。
EN: This plan was established with good intentions.

ZH: 在这个艰难的时刻，请给予我们善意的理解。
EN: Please give us your understanding in good faith during these difficult times.

ZH: 请不要恶意解读他的善意。
EN: Please do not misinterpret his good intentions with ill-will.

ZH: 我在你身上看到了善意的眼神。
EN: I see a look of goodwill in your eyes.

ZH: 善意的微笑让人感到宽慰。
EN: A kind smile brings comfort to people.

ZH: 善意的帮助让我深感感激。
EN: I am deeply grateful for the kind assistance.

ZH: 善意是建立良好关系的基石。
EN: Goodwill is the foundation for building good relationships.

ZH: 我用善意的心态去接受他人的批评。
EN: I accept criticism from others with a mindset of goodwill.

ZH: 她总是以善意的态度对待别人。
EN: She always treats others with a kind attitude.

ZH: 学会用善意的眼光看待世界。
EN: Learn to view the world with a benevolent perspective.

ZH: 下次请你多考虑一下他的善意。
EN: Next time, please consider his goodwill more carefully.
